sql:
SELECT c.country_name, 'GDP' AS metric_name
FROM countries c
WHERE (c.GDP / c.population) > (
  SELECT AVG(c2.GDP / c2.population)
  FROM countries c2
);

external_knowledge:
Economic growth generally refers to an increase in the production of goods and services in a country over time.
 Evaluation results for economic growth since 2020 are considered to be from '2020-01-01' onwards; 
 A higher average metric value indicates better performance in economic growth.
